Generate a Land-Use Suitability Table

Source: R/generate_landuse_table.R
generate_landuse_table.Rd

This function takes the path to a raster file containing land-use suitability values and converts it to a data frame. It filters the data to include only the cells that have a value of 1 in at least one of the land-use categories, indicating suitability.

Usage

generate_landuse_table(path)

Arguments

path

A string representing the file path to the raster file containing land-use suitability data.

Value

A data frame with the raster cells that have a suitability value of 1 in at least one of the land-use categories. The data frame includes the cell identifier and the corresponding suitability values for each land-use category.
